Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{} on medium-high heat. Add the @slow cooked beef{280%g} and juices from the packet. Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @Worcester sauce{15%g}, @water for the sauce{300%ml} and @sugar{1%tsp}.

Simmer with the lid on, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the beef is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, place the @demi garlic baguettes{2} onto a #baking tray{}. Bake on the middle shelf, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once the beef is tender, remove the lid. Shred the beef. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g}. Simmer on low, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} in handfuls, @butter{20%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Share the ragu and tagliatelle between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Serve the garlic bread alongside.

Enjoy!